timeline.bodyText:
What is this good for in the first place? Just for fun I tried this with both python2 AND python3 and it works in both versions:
#!/usr/bin/python2
foo=4200000000000000
if foo > 2**31-1:
print ("too big")
else:
print ("ok")
I'm a C guy, but there this would be a case that only affects the number "2", so to me this looks completely superfluous.
Nevertheless I will approve as it works with both python versions.
